{
  "action": "set_up",
  "reasoning": {
    "immediate_threat": "Phil Leotardo ain’t bluffin’. If I hand over Tony B, he’s gonna make a fuckin’ *example* outta him—slow, painful, send a message to every wiseguy in the country. That’s a stain on my family, on my name. But if I don’t, New York rolls in like the fuckin’ Fourth Cavalry, and we’re lookin’ at a war that’ll cost me soldiers, money, and respect. The Commission’ll side with Phil ‘cause he’s got the weight, and I’ll be left holdin’ a bloody shirt.",
    "cousin_loyalty": "Tony B’s my blood, but he’s also a loose cannon. He went and did this *thing* without my say-so, without even a fuckin’ *nod* in my direction. That’s disrespect. That’s *weakness*. If I let this slide, what’s stoppin’ the next guy from takin’ a shot at somethin’ big and draggin’ me into a war I didn’t ask for?",
    "strategic_move": "I gotta send a message—*to Phil, to the family, to the whole fuckin’ underworld*. If I off Tony B myself, quick and clean, I show Phil I handle my own. No war, no mess, no long torture session that makes me look like a pussy who can’t control his own. But I also gotta make sure Phil *sees* it as me takin’ care of business, not me bowin’ to him. So I set it up so it looks like Tony B got whacked by some outside player—maybe a rival family, maybe a rat he burned. Phil gets his pound of flesh in theory, I avoid a war, and my crew sees I don’t tolerate disrespect, even from family.",
    "long_game": "Phil’s gonna be pissed, sure, but he ain’t gonna start a war over a dead guy. He’ll respect that I didn’t hand him over like a fuckin’ *gift*, and he’ll respect that I didn’t let it slide. The Commission’ll see I kept the peace *my* way. And if Phil ever tries to pull this shit again, he’ll remember: Tony Soprano don’t bend, and he don’t forget.",
    "emotional_weight": "Yeah, it’s fucked up. Yeah, it’s my cousin. But in this life, blood don’t always mean shit if it’s gonna drag the whole family into the fire. I gotta think like a boss, not like a guy at a fuckin’ family barbecue. If I let this go, I’m not just losin’ Tony B—I’m losin’ *everything*.",
    "execution_plan": {
      "how": "I’ll have Paulie or Silvio take care of it. Make it look like a hit from the Luccheses or someone Phil’s got beef with. Maybe plant some evidence, leak a story. Phil’ll buy it ‘cause he *wants* to buy it—he don’t wanna go to war any more than I do. And if he don’t? Fuck him. I’ll be ready.",
      "timing": "Soon. Tonight. Before Phil starts movin’ his pieces. I gotta control the narrative, not react to it.",
      "message_to_crew": "I’ll make sure the word gets out: *‘Tony B stepped outta line, and the family handled it. That’s how we do things.’* No mercy, no exceptions. Keeps the soldiers in line and shows Phil I ain’t his bitch."
    }
  }
}
